  "texts": [
    "Interestingly, the Llama 2 7B model achieves a high BERTScore, even surpassing the 70B model, indicating a better semantic alignment.",
    "While the Llama 2 13B model slightly improves over the 7B in terms of BERTScore, the 70B model underperforms both smaller models, which suggests that increasing the number of parameters does not necessarily lead to better semantic understanding in this case.",
    "Moreover, the BLEU score for the Llama 2 70B model not only fails to improve but actually decreases compared to the 7B and 13B models.",
    "This suggests that the largest model struggles more with generating fluent and grammatically correct outputs, as BLEU measures n-gram overlap and fluency.",
    "Overall, while the 7B and 13B models exhibit strong performance in both fluency and semantic alignment, the 70B model shows a decline, particularly in BLEU, suggesting that larger models may encounter challenges in maintaining fluency and n-gram precision in the task of commonsense explanation generation."
  ],
